Author-Name: Sharon K. Long  
Author-Name: Karen Stockley  
Author-Name: Shanna Shulman  
Title: Have Gender Gaps in Insurance Coverage and Access to Care Narrowed under Health Reform? Findings from Massachusetts 
Abstract:
 Under its health reform legislation, Massachusetts has achieved near
 universal insurance coverage, along with significant gains in health care
 access and affordability. This paper examines the impacts of health reform
 in Massachusetts on differences in coverage, access, and affordability for
 women and men. We find that both women and men gained under health reform,
 with the gender gap in insurance coverage narrowed as men's coverage
 increased relative to that of women. However, the gaps in access and
 affordability of care have not narrowed--women in Massachusetts continue
 to report more unmet need for care and problems affording care than men.
