Author-Name: Alberto Davila  
Author-Name: Marie T. Mora  
Author-Name: Sue K. Stockly  
Title: Does Mestizaje Matter in the US? Economic Stratification of Mexican Immigrants 
Abstract:
 Using data from the 2003 New Immigrant Survey, this paper examines whether
 stratification as reflected by skin shade exists among newly legalized
 Mexican immigrants in the US. While we do not find evidence that skin
 color directly related to employment probabilities, complexion appeared to
 play a role in the likelihood of owning a home, having a bank account, and
 occupational status. As these outcomes partly reflect immigrants'
 pre-migration experiences, our findings suggest that the social
 stratification structure in Mexico might be sustained in the US among
 Mexican-origin populations.
