Author-Name: Paola Giuliano  
Author-Name: Nathan Nunn  
Title: Fertility and the Plough 
Abstract:
 This paper provides evidence that the form of agriculture traditionally
 practiced--intensive plough agriculture versus shifting hoe
 agriculture--affected historic norms and preferences about fertility, and
 that these norms persist, affecting observed fertility around the world
 today.
