Author-Name: Lars Ljungqvist  
Author-Name: Thomas J. Sargent  
Title: A Labor Supply Elasticity Accord? 
Abstract:
 A dispute about the size of the aggregate labor supply elasticity has been
 fortified by a contentious aggregation theory used by real business cycle
 theorists. The replacement of that aggregation theory with one more
 congenial to microeconomic observations opens possibilities for an accord
 about the aggregate labor supply elasticity. The new aggregation theory
 drops features to which empirical microeconomists objected and replaces
 them with life-cycle choices. Whether the new aggregation theory
 ultimately indicates a small or large macro labor supply elasticity will
 depend on how shocks and government institutions interact to put workers
 at interior solutions for career length.
