Author-Name: Janet Currie  
Author-Name: Michael Greenstone  
Author-Name: Enrico Moretti  
Title: Superfund Cleanups and Infant Health 
Abstract:
 We are the first to examine the effect of Superfund cleanups on infant
 health rather than focusing on proximity to a site. We study singleton
 births to mothers residing within 5km of a Superfund site between
 1989-2003 in five large states. Our "difference in differences" approach
 compares birth outcomes before and after a site clean-up for mothers who
 live within 2,000 meters of the site and those who live between
 2,000-5,000 meters of a site. We find that proximity to a Superfund site
 before cleanup is associated with a 20 to 25% increase in the risk of
 congenital anomalies.
