Author-Name: Karel Mertens  
Author-Name: Morten O. Ravn  
Title: Leverage and the Financial Accelerator in a Liquidity Trap 
Abstract:
 We show that the financial accelerator may be very large in a liquidity
 trap. We study a sticky price model with real estate and a financial
 friction specified as a collateral constraint. Expectations can lead the
 economy to a self-fulfilling liquidity trap equilibrium where the lower
 bound on the nominal interest rate binds. We model these equilibria as
 stochastic sunspots. As in the Great Depression, a liquidity trap entails
 house price depreciation and potentially large output losses. Higher
 leverage implies much larger output losses but at the same time rules out
 the existence of short-lived liquidity traps.
