Author-Name: Xavier Gabaix  
Title: Disasterization: A Simple Way to Fix the Asset Pricing Properties of Macroeconomic Models 
Abstract:
 A central difficulty in economics is to create a model with both good
 business cycle properties and asset pricing properties. I show how to
 solve this difficulty by a simple portable modeling device: the
 "disasterization" of models. Take an economy with good business cycle
 properties and create a new, "disasterized" economy, which is essentially
 identical to the original one except that disasters can destroy part of
 the capital stock and productivity. In such a disasterized economy, asset
 prices exhibit high and volatile risk premia, but macro variables remain
 unchanged. Perturbations of this benchmark allow for feedback from finance
 to macro.
