Author-Name: Geoffrey F. Joyce  
Author-Name: William B. Vogt  
Title: Part D Formulary and Benefit Design as a Risk-Steering Mechanism 
Abstract:
 Medicare Part D relies upon drug plan competition. Plans have enormous
 scope to design benefits and to set premiums, but they may not charge
 differential premiums based on risk. We use the formulary and benefit
 design of all Medicare prescription drug plans and pharmacy claims data to
 construct a simulation model of out-of-pocket drug spending. We use this
 simulation model to examine individual incentives in Medicare Part D for
 adverse selection. We find that high drug users have much stronger
 incentives to enroll in generous plans than do low users, thus there is
 significant scope for adverse selection.
