Author-Name: Min Lee  
Title: Can Tailored Communications Motivate Environmental Volunteers? A Natural Field Experiment 
Abstract:
 Volunteering is a significant component of economic activity, especially
 for environmental organizations. Environmental organizations that rely on
 volunteers communicate with them using a variety of media, such as
 newsletters. This is a field experiment investigating whether tailoring
 the content of these communications to the stated motivations of a
 volunteer has a positive effect on the number of hours he/she volunteers.
 For the non-profit in our study, we find that such tailoring has an effect
 only for volunteers motivated primarily by career concerns. We also find
 this to be robust to the volunteers being aware that the tailoring is
 occurring.
