Title: Does Market Experience Eliminate Market Anomalies? The Case of Exogenous Market Experience 
Abstract:
 A vibrant literature has emerged that suggests willingness to pay and
 willingness to accept measures of value are quite different for
 inexperienced consumers but that value differences erode with market
 experience. One potential shortcoming of this literature is that market
 experience is endogenous. This study presents a framed field experiment
 that exogenously induces market experience. Empirical findings support the
 premise that market experience, alone, can eliminate an important market
 anomaly
