Author-Name: Linda L. Tesar  
Title: The "Collapse in Quality" Hypothesis 
Abstract:
 This paper evaluates the hypothesis that during the 2008-2009 collapse in
 international trade, imports of higher quality goods experienced larger
 reductions compared to low-quality imports, using data on US imports
 disaggregated by HS-10 product category and source country. We find
 little, if any, robust econometric evidence in support of this hypothesis.
