Author-Name: Luc Renneboog  
Author-Name: Christophe Spaenjers  
Title: Art and Money 
Abstract:
 This paper investigates the impact of equity markets and top incomes on
 art prices. Using a newly constructed art market index, we demonstrate
 that equity market returns have had a significant impact on the price
 level in the art market over the last two centuries. We also find evidence
 that an increase in income inequality may lead to higher prices for art.
 Finally, the results of Johansen's cointegration tests strongly suggest
 the existence of a long-run relation between top incomes and art prices.
