Title: Markets and Morality 
Abstract:
 The paper addresses two issues. First, economics has evolved both as a
 positive science and, from moral philosophy, also as a normative
 discipline. Advancing the public good requires that public policy walk on
 both these legs. Second, the criticism has been forcefully made that
 markets undermine morality. This contention is refuted in several ways.
