Author-Name: Paul Goldsmith-Pinkham  
Author-Name: Peter Hull  
Author-Name: James Vickery  
Title: Credit Ratings and Security Prices in the Subprime MBS Market 
Abstract:
 We present and discuss preliminary evidence suggesting that credit ratings
 significantly influenced prices for subprime mortgage-backed securities
 issued in the period leading up to the recent financial crisis. Ratings
 are closely correlated with prices even controlling for a rich set of
 security- and loan-level controls. This incremental variation in ratings
 has much less predictive power for security defaults, however, based on
 findings to date from our ongoing research, suggesting prices were
 excessively sensitive to ratings relative to their informational content.
