Author-Name: Marquise McGraw  
Author-Name: John M. Quigley  
Title: The Diffusion of Energy Efficiency in Building 
Abstract:
 We analyze the diffusion of buildings certified for energy efficiency
 across US property markets. Using a panel of 48 metropolitan areas (MSAs)
 observed over the last 15 years, we model the geographic patterns and
 dynamics of building certification, relating industry composition, changes
 in economic conditions, characteristics of the local commercial property
 market, and the presence of human capital, to the cross-sectional
 variation in energy-efficient building technologies and the diffusion of
 those technologies over time. Understanding the determinants and the rate
 at which energy-efficient building practices diffuse is important for
 designing policies to affect resource consumption in the built
 environment.
