Author-Name: W. Kip Viscusi  
Author-Name: Joel Huber  
Author-Name: Jason Bell  
Title: Promoting Recycling: Private Values, Social Norms, and Economic Incentives 
Abstract:
 Evidence from a nationally representative sample of households illuminates
 the determinants of recycling behavior for plastic water bottles. Private
 values of the environment are influential in promoting recycling, as are
 personal norms for pro-environmental behavior. However, social norms with
 respect to the assessment of the household's recycling behaviors by others
 have little independent effect. Particularly influential are policies that
 create economic incentives to promote recycling either through state
 recycling laws that reduce the time and inconvenience costs of recycling
 or through bottle deposits. Effective policies can have a discontinuous
 effect at the individual level, transforming non-recyclers into avid
 recyclers.
