Author-Name: Louis Silvia  
Author-Name: Christopher Taylor  
Title: Does Concentration Matter? Measurement of Petroleum Merger Price Effects 
Abstract:
 We have estimated the price effects of two changes in market structure
 resulting from two changes in the ownership of gasoline refineries in the
 San Francisco Bay area: Tosco's purchase of Unocal's Rodeo refinery in
 April 1997 and UDS's purchase of Tosco's Avon refinery in August 2000.
 These events provide a relatively unique opportunity to test a price
 concentration relationship. If market concentration is related to price,
 then we should observe prices increase and then decrease by a similar
 amount following these transactions. We do not find evidence of a
 consistent price concentration relationship.
